description:
This is a 22 minute workout called '20-Minute Beginner Yoga Routine | Gentle Flow With Blocks' from the channel Evolv Yoga & Sound .
The workout falls under Flexibility/Yoga.
It's suitable for Beginner fitness levels.
The workout has a The Zen Flow and The Reboot Workout vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Join me for this 20-minute beginner yoga routine, designed to help you ease into your practice and build a strong foundation. Each pose is held for 3-5 breaths, giving you time to settle into your body, feel the stretch, and enjoy the flow. We'll be using two yoga blocks throughout the class to support your alignment and increase flexibility. If you don‚Äôt have yoga blocks, no worries! You can use books or water bottles as an alternative. Whether you're brand new to yoga or looking to refine your practice, this session is perfect for you!

Grab your mat and two blocks, and let's get started on this gentle, relaxing routine!
